Understanding Models in Data Science

## What I Learned

Today I came across an important idea:

“All models are wrong, but some are useful.”

This means that models are simplified representations of real-world situations. 
They cannot capture every detail, so they are never completely accurate.

## What is a Model?

A model is a way of representing real-world data to help us understand patterns, relationships, or make predictions.

Examples:
- Predicting sales based on past data
- Estimating future trends
- Understanding relationships between variables

## Why Models Are “Wrong”

- They simplify reality
- They ignore some variables
- They depend on assumptions

## Why Models Are Still Useful

- They help us make decisions
- They reveal patterns in data
- They allow predictions (even if not perfect)

## My Understanding

A model does not need to be perfect to be valuable. The goal is to make it useful enough to guide decisions.

## Questions

- How do we measure if a model is “useful”?
- What makes one model better than another?
